3/01 9:34:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> How hard it is for a warrior to keep all of their weapons skills capped down the road?  My str is 130 and dex is 75 and although my warrior is only level 7 the weapons seem slow to gain.  I've been told that a good warrior should keep all of his/her weapon skills capped.  I just want to know how hard that is to do?   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uerykaeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ErykaEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 72<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/01 9:45:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> Weapon skills will go slow at first, but you can usually get them to catch up in the mid to high teens; it's easier once you get dual wield / double attack especially for the 1 handed weapons. <p><p><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50985">Eryka</a> &lt;Arma Aquetatis&gt;<br>
DE Warrior of Lanys</font></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvoochawitchadoo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Voocha Witchadoo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/01 10:06:35 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> Nice!  So what about archery?  All I really use it for is pulling which is once and done.  Does that one go up faster than the others? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uamaretto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amaretto</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/01 11:29:43 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> If you don't care about dmg done by archery then don't worry about it too much. Even if you do zero damage it still gets the mob's attention for pulling. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ucorranndarklighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corrann Darklighter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/13/01 1:02:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://24.7.174.143/pics/cdhead.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> only used archery for pulling, and at lvl 46 its around 150 skill.  so it goes up fine all things considered.<br>
<br>
as for the other skills, remember it'll take you 10 times longer to level later on, so you'll have longer and longer fights, with more and more mobs to level, so you'll get plenty of chances to catch up lagging skills<br>
<br>
bash has gone from 50 to 150 in about 8 lvls. yes i bash, i'm a dorf, and i find it very effective. i DW and drop in a shield when it's time to bash<br>
<br>
 <p><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/cdlotmlogo.gif"><BR><br><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/motto.gif">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umorgannad.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Morganna D</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/01 9:59:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> Well, jst a thought. Weapon skills seems to max out really slowly once you reach lvl 51 and up. So b4 lvl 51, weapon skills generally go up pretty fast.<br>
<br>
Try to max out your weapon skills b4 you reach 51, so you dont have the nightmare I had of raising 2HB from 31 to my current 212 (took me lvls 51 - 54 to do that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  )<br>
<br>
Also, once at 51+, hitting blue mobs tend NOT to raise weapon skills. But if have the chance to fight some RED/YELLOW-con mobs, skills seems to raise at a pretty fast pace, if you can find em. <br>
<br>
<br>
P.S. At my stage, I'm generally getting skill raises by killing Veterans in Kael Drakkel (lvl 57 mobs) and they go up abt 2-3 points per mob, so not too bad <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/phrajile/MorgannaTiejinnie.jpg"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=vanzant>VanZant</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 101<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/16/01 11:07:54 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/vanzmojax/vanzysig00.jpg border=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> When I first started playing I didn't have the cash to carry around a lot of different weapons, but once I had an assortment I kept my 1 handed slashing, piercing, 2 handed slashing and archery up to par and maxed them out about every level.  Since 51, I've had a harder time keeping em all up, as well as trying to catch up my blunt skills. <p><img SRC="http://www.geocities.com/trunksz/VanZant.jpg" NOSAVE height=100 width=400><br><b><font color=black>Keep your fears to yourself, but share your courage!</font><br><font color=black>V</font><font color=navy>an</font><font color=black>Z</font><font color=Navy>ant</font>  <font color=black>B</font><font color=navy>rave</font><font color=black>S</font><font color=navy>word</font></b><br>
