<a href=mailto:vanhammer@hotmail.com><font color=navy><i><b>Vanhammer@hotmail.com</b></i></font></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/umelabojar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Melabojar</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.geocities.com/everquest_02118/button.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/17/01 7:41:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://razorbone.tripod.com/taunt.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> dang, i wish i could have worked bash during my adventures. Im now 46, think i would be able to get it up? Thanks<br>
<br>
Kret Swordstriker<br>
46 Halfling Warrior (2 blue bubs to 47 <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/ucorranndarklighter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Corrann Darklighter</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 29<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/18/01 7:07:49 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://24.7.174.143/pics/cdhead.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1> kret, like me, you would be starting a little late. but yes you can do it fairly easily.<br>
<br>
back when someone told me of the Mith staff, I borrowed one, went to a trainer and put 40 or 50 pts into it. I had no other use for those skill pts. I also put 40 or so into 1hb.  <br>
<br>
I then proceeded to go places where I could fight blues with friends and practice blunt since it wouldn't be life critical.  For you, I'd say a place like DL or GD, or another nice outdoor zone with controlled pulls.  Another option is to simply ask a group in a place like DL is you can whack on their pulls to practice skills. They usually won't mind.  you should be able to get 2hb up by the time you're 48, or dam near, and 1hb you could practice while DW'ing.<br>
<br>
corse a haste sash and a shamy or chanter would help too =)<br>
<br>
I used a Blackjack, 7/21 to do 1hb, since it was cheap and fast =)<br>
 <p><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/cdlotmlogo.gif"><BR><br><img src="http://24.7.174.143/files/motto.gif">
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/ugolliwog.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golliwog</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_greenspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/01 7:00:23 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Capping Weapon Skills</span><hr size=1>    For the most part, I've found that maxing my skills hasn't been a huge problem.  As a barbarian, bash is always maxed.  I used 2hs for most of my teens/twenties and then switched back and forth between 2hs 1hs 1hb and piercing.<br>
   My archery is at like 120 or something like that, I used to go buy some flethcing gear and make some 1dmg 150 range arrows and then while I'm waiting for a group, sit and fire arrows at their mobs (you should prolly ask them first if they mind heh).  Also did this with hand to hand.<br>
   Lastly, when trying to max skills like 2hb 2hs etc that don't do the most dmg you can is kinda hard because you want to do max dmg in a normal group in HS or Seb or whatever.  I usually use 2hb or 2hs on plane raids or other big raids where a few pts of dmg isn't going to make a huge difference. <p><p align="center"><img
